                             Service Description
                        </span>
                        <h2 class="cs-title">Professional Landscape Maintenance Built for the Desert</h2>
                        <p class="cs-text">Las Cruces yards face conditions that wear landscapes down faster than most of the country. Alkaline soil locks up nutrients, about 10 inches of rain a year stresses shallow-rooted plants, monsoon storms flood low spots, and triple-digit summers push irrigation systems hard. Without steady care, small issues turn into dead shrubs, failed drip lines, and weed-choked beds within a single season.</p>
                        <p class="cs-text">Landscape maintenance is the regular, scheduled care that keeps your yard healthy between bigger projects. It is not the same as a one-time cleanup or a new install. Real landscape maintenance services cover pruning, weed control, fertilization, seasonal adjustments, and irrigation tuning on a repeating schedule, so problems get caught early and plants stay on a growth path instead of a decline path.</p>
                        <p class="cs-text">We serve homeowners who want their weekends back, HOA boards who need common areas kept to standard, and commercial property managers protecting curb appeal. Whether the landscape was installed by Brainard's Greenscapes or someone else, we can pick up landscape and grounds maintenance and bring the property back on track.</p>
                        <ul class="cs-bullets">
                            <li>Owners with established xeriscape or desert-adapted plantings</li>
                            <li>HOA communities with common areas to maintain to guidelines</li>
                            <li>Commercial buildings with visible, street-facing landscaping</li>
                            <li>Properties where the previous landscaper is no longer a fit</li>
                            <li>New homeowners who inherited a yard and are not sure where to start</li>
                            <li>Second-home owners who need hands-on care while they are away</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
