        <section id="faq-506">
            <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern">
            <div class="cs-container">
                <div class="cs-content">
                    <span class="cs-topper">
                        <span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                        <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow">
                         FAQ
                    </span>
                    <h2 class="cs-title">Landscape Maintenance Questions</h2>
                </div>
                <ul class="cs-faq-list">
                    <li class="cs-faq-item">
                        <details class="cs-faq">
                            <summary class="cs-faq-summary">
                                <span class="cs-faq-question">How often should you maintain your landscape in Las Cruces?</span>
                                <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                                    <svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24">
                                        <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"/>
                                    </svg>
                                </span>
                            </summary>
                            <div class="cs-faq-body">
                                <p>Most Las Cruces properties do best with bi-weekly visits from March through October, when desert plants grow hard, weeds surge, and irrigation runs on overtime. From November through February, monthly visits are usually enough to handle light pruning, dormant weed control, and controller adjustments. Pure xeriscape yards can often drop to monthly year-round. Properties with turf, flowering shrubs, or fruit trees typically need weekly or bi-weekly visits during peak season.</p>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </li>
                    <li class="cs-faq-item">
                        <details class="cs-faq">
                            <summary class="cs-faq-summary">
                                <span class="cs-faq-question">What is landscape maintenance and what does it include?</span>
                                <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                                    <svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24">
                                        <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"/>
                                    </svg>
                                </span>
                            </summary>
                            <div class="cs-faq-body">
                                <p>Landscape maintenance is the regular, scheduled care that keeps a yard healthy between bigger projects. It is different from a single yard cleanup or a new installation. Our plans typically include pruning and shaping, weed control (pre-emergent plus hand removal), fertilization matched to desert soil pH, seasonal cleanup, mulch or gravel replenishment, and drip irrigation checks. A detailed landscape maintenance checklist is built specifically for your property.</p>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </li>
                    <li class="cs-faq-item">
                        <details class="cs-faq">
                            <summary class="cs-faq-summary">
                                <span class="cs-faq-question">How much does landscape maintenance cost in Las Cruces?</span>
                                <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                                    <svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24">
                                        <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"/>
                                    </svg>
                                </span>
                            </summary>
                            <div class="cs-faq-body">
                                <p>
                                    Monthly landscape maintenance cost depends on property size, plant count, irrigation complexity, and visit frequency. A small residential xeriscape on a monthly plan starts at one rate, a half-acre property with turf and mature trees on bi-weekly service runs higher, and HOA common areas are bid against the specific scope. After the free on-site walk, you get a written quote with a fixed monthly price. Call 
                                    <a href="tel:575-635-8883">(575) 635-8883</a>
                                     for a free estimate.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </li>
                    <li class="cs-faq-item">
                        <details class="cs-faq">
                            <summary class="cs-faq-summary">
                                <span class="cs-faq-question">Do you maintain landscapes you didn’t install?</span>
                                <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                                    <svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24">
                                        <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"/>
                                    </svg>
                                </span>
                            </summary>
                            <div class="cs-faq-body">
                                <p>Yes. A large share of our maintenance clients came to us from other companies or from homes where the previous owner did their own care. During the first walk, we inventory the plants, flag any immediate issues, and build a plan to get everything back on track. In most cases a single reset visit is enough to bring a neglected yard into a healthy maintenance cycle.</p>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </li>
                    <li class="cs-faq-item">
                        <details class="cs-faq">
                            <summary class="cs-faq-summary">
                                <span class="cs-faq-question">Do you offer one-time cleanups or only recurring plans?</span>
                                <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                                    <svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24">
                                        <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"/>
                                    </svg>
                                </span>
                            </summary>
                            <div class="cs-faq-body">
                                <p>We offer both. Spring prep, fall cleanup, monsoon debris removal, and "neglected yard" resets are available for homeowners not ready for a recurring plan. Many clients start with a one-time visit, see the result, and then switch to a monthly plan once the property is back on a healthy baseline.</p>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </li>
                    <li class="cs-faq-item">
                        <details class="cs-faq">
                            <summary class="cs-faq-summary">
                                <span class="cs-faq-question">Can you handle HOA common areas and commercial properties?</span>
                                <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                                    <svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24">
                                        <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"/>
                                    </svg>
                                </span>
                            </summary>
                            <div class="cs-faq-body">
                                <p>Yes. As a full-service HOA landscape maintenance company, we service HOA common areas, apartment communities, office parks, and retail centers across Las Cruces and southern Doña Ana County. HOA and commercial contracts include written post-visit reports, certificates of insurance, additional insureds on request, and a dedicated account contact for boards or property managers. We can bid to your RFP format or provide line-item pricing for budget meetings.</p>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </li>
                    <li class="cs-faq-item">
                        <details class="cs-faq">
                            <summary class="cs-faq-summary">
                                <span class="cs-faq-question">Do you handle irrigation issues during maintenance visits?</span>
                                <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                                    <svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24">
                                        <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"/>
                                    </svg>
                                </span>
                            </summary>
                            <div class="cs-faq-body">
                                <p>
                                    Every maintenance visit includes a basic irrigation check: emitter flow, head alignment, and controller adjustment for the season. For larger repairs, system upgrades, or a full drip retrofit, our 
                                    <a href="/services/irrigation/">irrigation team</a>
                                     handles those as a separate project so maintenance visits stay predictable on price.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </li>
                    <li class="cs-faq-item">
                        <details class="cs-faq">
                            <summary class="cs-faq-summary">
                                <span class="cs-faq-question">Will the same crew come every visit?</span>
                                <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                                    <svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24">
                                        <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"/>
                                    </svg>
                                </span>
                            </summary>
                            <div class="cs-faq-body">
                                <p>Yes. Once you approve a plan, you are assigned a crew that handles your property on every visit. Our people stay with the company for years, so continuity is the norm, not the exception. If your regular lead is out, we send someone who has worked with the crew so nothing falls through.</p>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>
